*******************************************************************************
* Interdigitated metal fringe capacitor (cap_mfringe)
*
* Metal stack M1..M4, alternating-finger topology.
* Areacap model: base capacitance density depends on bottom metal,
* each additional metal layer adds 0.55 fF/um^2.
*
*   areacap = base + (mmax - mmin) * 0.55  [fF/um^2]
*     base  = 0.67 fF/um^2 if mmin == 1 (Metal1)
*           = 0.55 fF/um^2 otherwise
*   C = areacap * w * l
*
* Parameters:
*   w    - capacitor width  [m] (default 2.0 um)
*   l    - capacitor length [m] (default 2.0 um)
*   mmin - bottom metal layer index, 1=M1 .. 4=M4 (default 1)
*   mmax - top metal layer index, 1=M1 .. 4=M4    (default 4)
*
* Terminals:
*   c1 - plate 1
*   c2 - plate 2
*
*******************************************************************************
*
*                c1
*                |  c2
*                |  |
.subckt cap_mfringe c1 c2
.param w=2.0e-6 l=2.0e-6 mmin=1 mmax=4

* Areacap [fF/um^2]: 0.67 base for M1, 0.55 otherwise, +0.55 per extra layer
* Capacitance [F]: areacap * w_um * l_um * 1e-15
+ cval='((mmin==1 ? 0.67 : 0.55) + (mmax - mmin) * 0.55) * (w * 1e6) * (l * 1e6) * 1e-15'

C1 c1 c2 'cval'

.ends cap_mfringe
